 5. Audit vs Observability

 Add a short distinction:

 Audit
   product/domain history
   who did what, to which resource, when, and why if available
   durable, queryable, user-visible or admin-visible

 Observability
   operational telemetry
   metrics, logs, traces, latency, failures
   used for operating the system

 Chronicon owns audit/history.

 Observability should be separate and may eventually live in another infrastructure concern or fundamentum-level telemetry abstraction.

 Do not implement observability here.

